...when the Natives took you.

193
00:22:57,527 --> 00:23:02,317
- Oh, that was you?
- Yeah. I thought you was killed.

194
00:23:04,927 --> 00:23:06,838
They just locked me up,
you know that?

195
00:23:07,007 --> 00:23:08,918
This long?

196
00:23:09,087 --> 00:23:13,717
Well, I kept trying to escape, you know.
They add on time for that.

197
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:17,241
So, what are you doing back here?

198
00:23:17,887 --> 00:23:19,843
I guess I missed the place.

199
00:23:26,407 --> 00:23:28,079
Bowery Boys.

200
00:23:40,007 --> 00:23:41,406
Get back here!

201
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:44,286
The Five Points, Paradise Square.

202
00:23:44,447 --> 00:23:47,359
The streets here are always lively
of an evening.

203
00:23:48,327 --> 00:23:49,965
Who are the gangs around now?

204
00:23:50,127 --> 00:23:52,004
The Daybreak Boys
and the Swamp Angels.

205
00:23:52,167 --> 00:23:54,237
They work the river, looting ships.

206
00:23:54,407 --> 00:23:57,001
The frog Hollows shanghai sailors
by the Bloody Angle.

207
00:23:57,167 --> 00:24:00,523
The Shirt Tails was rough,
but they've become a bunch of dandies...

208
00:24:00,687 --> 00:24:03,485
...Iolling around Murderers' Alley,
looking like Chinamen.

209
00:24:03,727 --> 00:24:06,321
Hell-Cat Maggie, she tried to open
her own grog shop.

210
00:24:06,487 --> 00:24:09,001
She drunk her own liquor
and got throwed on the street.

211
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,601
- Beautiful.
- Now she's on the lay for anything.

212
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:14,201
The Plug Uglies are from deep
in the old country.

213
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:16,517
Got their own language
no one understands.

214
00:24:16,687 --> 00:24:19,918
They love to fight the cops.
The Night Walkers of Ragpicker's Row.

215
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:22,927
They work on their backs
and kill with their hands.

216
