- You have to register.
- You can't force me to join.

1209
02:01:52,087 --> 02:01:53,679
- Have you got $300?
- Of course not.

1210
02:01:53,847 --> 02:01:57,157
- Who's got $300?
- Lf you're drafted, release from service...

1211
02:01:57,327 --> 02:02:00,603
...can only be secured for $300,
according to the Conscription Act.

1212
02:02:00,767 --> 02:02:03,281
- Otherwise, you have to serve!
- Who the hell's got $300?

1213
02:02:03,447 --> 02:02:06,962
You have to serve, sir,
unless you have $300!

1214
02:02:07,127 --> 02:02:09,004
- Boys!
- Go back to where you came from!

1215
02:02:09,167 --> 02:02:13,365
I'm born in this country. You immigrated
here. You will fight for this country!

1216
02:02:13,527 --> 02:02:16,087
Sweet Jesus!
War does terrible things to men.

1217
02:02:16,247 --> 02:02:22,004
- Get back uptown where you belong!
- $300? So i�s another rich man's war.

1218
02:02:22,167 --> 02:02:25,159
Sir, I request an audience
with this man.

1219
02:02:27,127 --> 02:02:29,197
No one speak English
in New York anymore?

1220
02:02:29,367 --> 02:02:31,403
- Don't understand.
- You do speak English.

1221
02:02:33,247 --> 02:02:37,479
I wonder if Miss Everdeane could
angle her rifle in some other direction.

1222
02:02:42,607 --> 02:02:47,158
I wonder, Mr. Vallon, if you understand
the true value of this sort of publicity.

1223
02:02:50,927 --> 02:02:54,715
The archbishop himself, shoulder to
shoulder with the Irish in the Five Points.

1224
02:02:55,247 --> 02:02:58,284
I'm offering to form an alliance
with you against Bill Cutting...

1225
02:02:58,447 --> 02:03:01,041
...and his slate
of Nativist candidates.

1226
02:03:01,207 --> 02:03:05,041
I'll negotiate a handsome fee for every
Irish vote you send Tammany's way...

1227
02:03:05,207 --> 02:03:07,437
...in the coming elections.

1228
02:03:08,847 --> 02:03:11,884
I need a new friend
in the Five Points, son.

1229
02:03:14,807 --> 02:03:17,162
I'd like that friend to be you.

1230
02:03:20,247 --> 02:03:22,841
Now, just a moment, Mr. Tweed.

1231
02:03:23,007 --> 02:03:26,079
Suppose we do
get you those votes.

1232
02:03:28,327 --> 02:03:30,477
Would you back an Irish candidate
of my choosing?

1233
02:03:30,647 --> 02:03:33,525
- I don't think so.
- What if we get you all the Irish votes?

1234
02:03:33,807 --> 02:03:37,356
That will only happen
in the reign of Queen Dick.

1235
02:03:39,287 --> 02:03:41,403
- Beg your pardon?
- It will never happen.

1236
02:03:41,567 --> 02:03:44,877
I might be persuaded to back an
Irish candidate for, say, alderman.

1237
02:03:45,047 --> 02:03:47,720
- Alderman?
- We've already got Irish aldermen.

1238
02:03:47,887 --> 02:03:51,118
- So we have. Tha�s why...
- Well, wha�s bigger than alderman?

1239
02:03:52,527 --> 02:03:56,156
Sheriff. Sheriff.
All right, Mr. Tweed.

1240
02:03:56,327 --> 02:04:00,115
You back an Irishman for sheriff
of the city and county of New York...

1241
02:04:00,287 --> 02:04:01,606
...and we'll get him elected.

1242
02:04:01,767 --> 02:04:04,998
I love the Irish, but higher than alderman
you shall never climb.

1243
02:04:05,167 --> 02:04:07,556
- Well, why not?
- For one thing, no man living...

1244
02:04:07,727 --> 02:04:09,445
...can consolidate the Irish vote.
- I can.

1245
02:04:09,607 --> 02:04:11,723
And for another,
I mean no effrontery...

1246
02:04:11,887 --> 02:04:15,960
...no one's yet found an Irish candidate
for sheriff worth voting for.

1247
02:04:18,247 --> 02:04:19,566
Monk.

1248
02:04:20,567 --> 02:04:21,841
Here.

1249
02:04:26,167 --> 02:04:28,727
He's to have me looking as sober
as me own grandfather.

1250
02:04:28,887 --> 02:04:32,880
- Another great man, I'm sure.
- A thorough drunken bastard.

1251
02:04:34,807 --> 02:04:36,525
Could I say what I want?

1252
02:04:37,647 --> 02:04:39,877
Well, tha�s why I wanted you.

1253
02:04:40,047 --> 02:04:42,845
Our elected representatives
are a gang of thieves...

1254
02:04:43,007 --> 02:04:44,679
...who swear to better our lot...

1255
02:04:44,847 --> 02:04:47,600
...while dipping their hands deep
into our pockets.

1256
02:04:47,767 --> 02:04:51,316
I stand shoulder to shoulder with
community leaders like Bill Cutting...

1257
02:04:51,727 --> 02:04:55,436
...against any and all inroads
into our fine democracy.

1258
02:04:55,607 --> 02:04:59,646
I'll see to it that no one takes away what
you've earned by pluck and application.

1259
02:04:59,807 --> 02:05:01,798
- To invading hordes of Hibernians!

1260
02:05:01,967 --> 02:05:05,846
You go to the polls and you put your
mark next to the name Walter McGinn.

1261
02:05:06,007 --> 02:05:10,478
- Against the potato eaters, like them
over there, thieving our jobs!

1262
02:05:10,647 --> 02:05:12,922
Why should so many
Irish die down south...

1263
02:05:13,087 --> 02:05:17,524
...when the first war to win is not down
in Dixie, but right here in these streets?

1264
02:05:19,287 --> 02:05:21,960
And who's the finest street fighter
in the Five Points?

1265
02:05:22,167 --> 02:05:24,237
- Monk!
- Tha�s right.

1266
02:05:24,407 --> 02:05:27,046
Now, let the whole damn city hear it!

1267
02:05:28,407 --> 02:05:30,159
That man was right born for this.

1268
02:05:30,327 --> 02:05:33,239
Well, he's killed 44 men,
laid low a couple hundred more.

1269
02:05:33,407 --> 02:05:34,999
- Is that right?
- Tha�s right.

1270
02:05:35,167 --> 02:05:37,158
I should have run him for mayor.

1271
02:05:39,287 --> 02:05:42,438
All right, line them up.
L�s election day!

1272
02:05:42,927 --> 02:05:46,124
Not so fast,
you little yellow bastard!

1273
02:05:46,327 --> 02:05:48,079
Come on!

1274
02:05:51,647 --> 02:05:53,558
Come on, you bastard,
we need your vote.

1275
02:05:53,727 --> 02:05:57,003
Bastard? I fought for you, nigger.
I lost an arm for you.

1276
02:05:57,167 --> 02:05:58,919
Well, tha�s a start.
Now, come on.

1277
02:05:59,087 --> 02:06:00,759
Rise and shine.
Rise and shine.

1278
02:06:00,927 --> 02:06:03,964
In this great country of ours,
even the hop fiends get to vote!

1279
02:06:05,207 --> 02:06:06,959
Less art and more haste, Don.

1280
02:06:07,127 --> 02:06:09,516
- Where are you going?
- I already voted today.

1281
02:06:09,687 --> 02:06:12,565
Cast for Monk and Tammany,
by God. Twice.

1282
02:06:12,727 --> 02:06:16,402
Twice? Only twice? You call that doing
your civic duty? Come with me.

1283
02:06:16,567 --> 02:06:19,081
Oh, no, you don't.
Get back and sit down.

1284
02:06:19,247 --> 02:06:21,238
Here's another one.
Clean him up good.

1285
02:06:21,407 --> 02:06:23,967
Shave their beards and send them back
to vote again.

1286
02:06:24,127 --> 02:06:26,880
All right, boys. Vote Monk, Tammany.
Monk, Tammany!

1287
02:06:27,047 --> 02:06:30,005
So, gentlemen, what our great city
needs is a new courthouse.

1288
02:06:30,167 --> 02:06:32,920
I propose it should be a modest,
economical structure.

1289
02:06:33,087 --> 02:06:34,805
Excuse me one moment.

1290
02:06:34,967 --> 02:06:38,357
Monk's already won by 3000
more votes than there are voters.

1291
02:06:38,527 --> 02:06:41,917
Three? Make it 20, 30. We don't need
a victory. We need a Roman triumph!

1292
02:06:42,087 --> 02:06:46,160
- But we don't have any more ballots.
- Remember the first rule of politics:

1293
02:06:46,327 --> 02:06:49,558
The ballots don't make the results,
the counters make the results.

1294
02:06:49,727 --> 02:06:50,796
Keep counting.

1295
02:07:21,367 --> 02:07:23,278
L�s from Bill.

1296
02:07:26,567 --> 02:07:28,080
Monk.

1297
02:07:47,007 --> 02:07:49,885
Citizens of the Five Points...

1298
02:07:50,367 --> 02:07:54,121
...Mr. Bill Cutting is attempting
to draw me into an argument...

1299
02:07:54,287 --> 02:07:58,678
...that would no doubt end in bloodshed
and the compromising of my office.

1300
02:07:59,327 --> 02:08:01,204
What do you think?

1301
02:08:02,087 --> 02:08:05,602
Should I engage in silence
this relic of the ancient law?

1302
02:08:05,767 --> 02:08:11,922
Or shall I be your chosen voice
in a new testament, in the new world?

1303
02:08:17,647 --> 02:08:19,365
There you are, Bill.

1304
02:08:20,927 --> 02:08:22,838
The people have spoken.

1305
02:08:24,287 --> 02:08:28,200
The very notion of violent reprisal
benumbs them.

1306
02:08:30,367 --> 02:08:31,925
Come on up.

1307
02:08:32,487 --> 02:08:35,763
Le�s see if we can resolve
our grievances the democratic way.

1308
02:08:58,087 --> 02:09:02,683
That, my friends,
is the minority vote.

1309
02:09:03,687 --> 02:09:07,566
Now you've tasted my mutton.
How do you like it?

1310
02:09:07,727 --> 02:09:09,046
Look.

1311
02:09:09,207 --> 02:09:11,641
I want you to see this.

1312
02:09:14,367 --> 02:09:16,403
This is you. Right here.

1313
02:09:16,567 --> 02:09:20,276
Notch 45, you Irish bog bastard.

1314
02:09:31,287 --> 02:09:34,643
Why don't you burn him,
see if his ashes turn green.

1315
02:09:39,727 --> 02:09:42,002
Fortune favors the bold!

1316
02:09:53,927 --> 02:09:57,840
- You killed an elected official?
- Who elected him?

1317
02:09:58,007 --> 02:10:01,044
You don't know what
you've done to yourself.

1318
02:10:06,327 --> 02:10:08,761
I know your works.

1319
02:10:09,367 --> 02:10:11,483
You are neither cold nor hot.

1320
02:10:11,647 --> 02:10:15,765
So because you are lukewarm,
I will spew you out of my mouth.

1321
02:10:17,287 --> 02:10:19,676
You can build your filthy world
without me.

1322
02:10:19,847 --> 02:10:22,202
I took the father.
Now I'll take the son.

1323
02:10:22,367 --> 02:10:27,077
You tell young Vallon I'm gonna
paint Paradise Square with his blood.

1324
02:10:27,327 --> 02:10:28,840
Two coats.

1325
02:10:29,407 --> 02:10:31,967
I'll festoon my bedchamber
with his guts.

1326
02:10:32,127 --> 02:10:34,482
As for you,
Mr. Tammany-fucking-Hall...

1327
02:10:34,647 --> 02:10:36,478
...you come down
to the Points again...

1328
02:10:36,647 --> 02:10:40,003
...and you'll be dispatched
by mine own hand.

1329
02:10:41,727 --> 02:10:46,881
Now get back to your celebration
and let me eat in peace. I paid you fair.

1330
02:11:09,727 --> 02:11:11,365
Stop.

1331
02:11:12,327 --> 02:11:13,840
Raise.

1332
02:11:55,167 --> 02:11:57,317
You son of a bitch!

1333
02:12:01,007 --> 02:12:02,918
Challenge.

1334
02:12:04,247 --> 02:12:06,522
Challenge accepted.

1335
02:12:56,087 --> 02:12:59,363
And then it came,
the first day of the draft.

1336
02:12:59,527 --> 02:13:04,681
Thomas O'Neill. Andrew Lewis.
Joseph flynn.

1337
02:13:04,847 --> 02:13:07,919
They read out the draftees ' names
like they was dead already.

1338
02:13:08,087 --> 02:13:12,239
Andrew Martin. J.B. Gleason.

1339
02:13:12,407 --> 02:13:15,046
- The O'Connell Guard.
- The Plug Uglies.

1340
02:13:15,207 --> 02:13:18,324
- As for us, the tribes were gathered.
- Forty Thieves.

1341
02:13:18,647 --> 02:13:21,036
- The Chichesters.
- The drums was beating.

1342
02:13:21,207 --> 02:13:22,481
The Dead Rabbits.

1343
02:13:22,647 --> 02:13:25,480
- The American Guard.
- The Atlantic Guard.

1344
02:13:25,647 --> 02:13:28,207
- The Slaughter Housers.
- The Bowery Boys.

1345
02:13:28,367 --> 02:13:30,597
The Confederation
of American Natives.

1346
02:13:31,967 --> 02:13:33,036
James Mooney.

1347
02:13:33,207 --> 02:13:36,563
But all we could see
was the hand in front of us.

1348
02:13:36,727 --> 02:13:38,638
Sean O'Connell.

1349
02:13:38,807 --> 02:13:42,800
G.W. Morris. John Doyle.

1350
02:13:42,967 --> 02:13:45,527
- When?
- Whenever you like.

1351
02:13:45,687 --> 02:13:47,803
- Daybreak tomorrow.
- Ground?

1352
02:13:47,967 --> 02:13:50,003
Paradise Square.

1353
02:13:50,167 --> 02:13:51,885
Weapons?

1354
02:13:52,047 --> 02:13:57,075
- That I leave up to you.
- Bricks, bats, axes, knives...

1355
02:13:57,407 --> 02:13:58,806
Pistols?

1356
02:14:00,287 --> 02:14:01,686
No pistols.

1357
02:14:02,767 --> 02:14:04,723
Good boy.

1358
02:14:07,167 --> 02:14:10,079
The terms are resolved.
The council's concluded.

1359
02:14:11,927 --> 02:14:15,806
Thomas McEvoy. W.H. Miles.

1360
02:14:15,967 --> 02:14:18,925
- To hell with your damned draft!
- Give them hellfire, boys!

1361
02:14:19,087 --> 02:14:20,566
Rip them apart!

1362
02:14:27,327 --> 02:14:29,761
Kill the rich bastards!

1363
02:14:35,727 --> 02:14:37,285
Uptown!

1364
02:14:38,807 --> 02:14:40,525
You're not getting my son!

1365
02:14:45,847 --> 02:14:48,407
Uptown at the draft office...

1366
02:14:48,567 --> 02:14:53,402
...the cops broke a few skulls,
and everybody run away.

1367
02:14:54,367 --> 02:14:56,676
But the word was spreading...

1368
02:14:56,847 --> 02:14:58,644
...and the dark.

1369
02:14:59,767 --> 02:15:01,086
Up on Fifth Avenue...

1370
02:15:01,247 --> 02:15:04,444
...the Schermerhorns and their mob
breathed a little easy.

1371
02:15:04,607 --> 02:15:07,485
Just a brief burst of anger
over Mr. Lincoln's draft.

1372
02:15:07,647 --> 02:15:09,797
Entirely justifiable in my view.

1373
02:15:09,967 --> 02:15:13,516
- There are two sides to that question...
- There are several sides...

1374
02:15:13,687 --> 02:15:16,121
...but only one right side,
as with any question...

1375
02:15:16,287 --> 02:15:18,482
...that involves the abuse
of executive power.

1376
02:15:18,647 --> 02:15:20,877
In any case, Mr. Greeley...

1377
02:15:21,047 --> 02:15:23,641
...we can all be thankful
that it wasn't any worse.

1378
02:15:23,807 --> 02:15:26,799
It may be worse yet. I saw them.
I don't know what to think.

1379
02:15:26,967 --> 02:15:30,039
Now what is it that you are
so fond of saying, Mr. Tweed?

1380
02:15:30,207 --> 02:15:32,562
Mr. Greeley, you won't like this.
But what is it?

1381
02:15:32,727 --> 02:15:33,716
I don't remember.

1382
02:15:33,887 --> 02:15:38,438
"You can always hire one half
of the poor to kill the other half."

1383
02:15:48,287 --> 02:15:50,517
I've come to say goodbye.

1384
02:15:50,687 --> 02:15:53,520
I've booked passage for California.

1385
02:15:55,927 --> 02:15:58,600
Jenny, give me one more day,
and I'll go with you.

1386
02:15:58,767 --> 02:16:00,997
You'll be dead by then.

1387
02:16:01,527 --> 02:16:04,837
- Well, what would you have me do?
- I don't know.

1388
02:16:07,367 --> 02:16:10,962
- This will all be finished tomorrow.
- No, it won't.

1389
02:16:12,527 --> 02:16:14,006
No.

1390
02:16:14,407 --> 02:16:17,399
This whole place
is gonna burn anyway.

1391
02:16:25,127 --> 02:16:29,678
I've heard that the poor are going
from door to door in the Five Points...

1392
02:16:29,847 --> 02:16:33,237
...asking those supporters
who wish to see further riots...

1393
02:16:33,407 --> 02:16:36,399
...to place a lighted candle
in the window.

1394
02:16:36,807 --> 02:16:38,798
Irish, Poles, Germans, all of them.

1395
02:16:39,567 --> 02:16:45,517
Mr. Greeley, the city is not mad.
I prophesy a very dark night.

1396
02:17:06,847 --> 02:17:10,522
Nobody goes to work today!
We'll shut the factories down!

1397
02:17:10,687 --> 02:17:14,919
When the sun rose next,
the city had split in half.

1398
02:17:15,087 --> 02:17:16,839
From all over New York they came:

1399
02:17:17,007 --> 02:17:19,726
Ironworkers, factory boys,
street cleaners...

1400
02:17:19,887 --> 02:17:21,400
...Irish, Polish, German...

1401
02:17:21,567 --> 02:17:24,240
...anyone who never cared
about slavery or the Union...

1402
02:17:24,407 --> 02:17:26,875
...anyone who couldn 't buy his way out.

1403
02:17:27,047 --> 02:17:29,925
"Let the sons of the rich
go and die, " they cried.

1404
02:17:30,087 --> 02:17:32,999
"Let the sons of the poor stay home."

1405
02:17:34,327 --> 02:17:36,397
The earth was shaking now.

1406
02:17:36,567 --> 02:17:39,161
But I was about my father's business.

1407
02:17:44,047 --> 02:17:46,163
A bunch of fifth Avenue scums!

1408
02:17:53,047 --> 02:17:57,359
Almighty Lord,
you are the dagger in my hand.

1409
02:17:58,607 --> 02:18:00,882
Guide my hand
on this day of vengeance.

1410
02:18:01,047 --> 02:18:04,881
We give thanks to the Lord,
for he is good.

1411
02:18:05,047 --> 02:18:09,199
With you, the swift cannot flee,
nor the strong escape.

1412
02:18:09,367 --> 02:18:13,360
Let my sword devour until its thirst
is quenched with blood...

1413
02:18:13,527 --> 02:18:15,438
...and my enemies sleep forever.

1414
02:18:15,607 --> 02:18:17,882
For you are the Lord God of Retribution.

1415
02:18:18,047 --> 02:18:20,402
For the Lord crushes the wicked.

1416
02:18:20,567 --> 02:18:23,081
The Lord is merciful...

1417
02:18:23,687 --> 02:18:27,316
...and his love endures forever.

1418
02:18:27,847 --> 02:18:29,166
- Amen.
- Amen.

1419
02:18:29,327 --> 02:18:30,442
Amen.

1420
02:18:36,207 --> 02:18:39,119
- Run away, you sons of bitches!
- Come on out!

1421
02:18:41,567 --> 02:18:45,526
- Upstairs! Get the women upstairs!
- Father! Father!

1422
02:18:49,207 --> 02:18:51,596
Le�s take the bastards!

1423
02:18:52,567 --> 02:18:56,401
From 18th Precinct: The mob are sacking
houses, 27th Street and Seventh Ave.

1424
02:18:56,567 --> 02:18:57,886
We have no force to send.

1425
02:18:58,047 --> 02:19:01,198
16th Precinct: All the stores
are closing on Eighth Avenue...

1426
02:19:01,367 --> 02:19:03,278
...from fear of the mob in 17th Street.

1427
02:19:03,447 --> 02:19:05,836
Show us what you got,
you cowardly bastards!

1428
02:19:07,567 --> 02:19:10,525
From 4th: The rioters are robbing
colored boarding houses...

1429
02:19:10,687 --> 02:19:13,042
...and setting them on fire.
From 21st:

1430
02:19:14,367 --> 02:19:17,200
The mob have just broken open
gun store and are arming.

1431
02:19:21,687 --> 02:19:24,121
- Get the nigger! Kill him!
- Tear Tammany down!

1432
02:19:24,287 --> 02:19:27,359
The marshal's office is burning down.
The police is of no avail.

1433
02:19:27,527 --> 02:19:28,562
Show yourself, Tweed!

1434
02:19:28,727 --> 02:19:30,365
Two colored men brought
in almost dead.

1435
02:19:32,207 --> 02:19:35,597
There are more Negroes who need help.
They're being attacked all over.

1436
02:19:35,767 --> 02:19:37,485
Hey! There's a $300 man.
Get him!

1437
02:19:37,647 --> 02:19:40,639
Did your daddy buy you out of the Army?
Can he buy me out too?

1438
02:19:41,967 --> 02:19:45,846
There's danger of mob attacking armory,
corner 21st Street, Second Avenue.

1439
02:19:46,007 --> 02:19:48,123
There is about 500 stand of arms in it.

1440
02:19:53,927 --> 02:19:56,885
The line is dead!
They're trying to cut all the wires!

1441
02:20:00,047 --> 02:20:03,323
From 1st: Riot at Pier 4, North River.
They have killed Negroes.

1442
02:20:03,487 --> 02:20:06,365
A crowd is here
and are going to destroy this station.

1443
02:20:09,207 --> 02:20:11,323
Get her bag! Get her bag!

1444
02:20:13,367 --> 02:20:14,356
From 18th Precinct:

1445
02:20:14,527 --> 02:20:19,078
The mob have attacked the armory.
There is danger of firing the building.

1446
02:20:19,247 --> 02:20:21,681
All 300 police wounded
or unaccounted for.

1447
02:20:21,847 --> 02:20:23,326
Find the military
and send them...

1448
02:20:23,487 --> 02:20:27,639
From 20th: Send 100 men to disperse
mob assailing Mayor Opdyke's house.

1449
02:20:27,807 --> 02:20:29,479
Building set on fire by the mob.

1450
02:20:32,207 --> 02:20:35,438
Barnum 's American Muzeum on fire.
Animals are escaping.

1451
02:20:35,607 --> 02:20:37,962
Let go! Let go!

1452
02:20:38,527 --> 02:20:41,041
Hush the shickster! Hold her down!

1453
02:20:52,287 --> 02:20:56,121
Gunboat Liberty and ironclad Passaic
now lying off the foot of Wall Street.

1454
02:20:56,287 --> 02:20:58,198
They are ready to open fire on the mob.

1455
02:20:58,367 --> 02:21:00,676
- Very large mob going
to attack Tribune office.

1456
02:21:02,047 --> 02:21:04,607
From 16th: Mob 's coming down
to station. We have no men.

1457
02:21:04,767 --> 02:21:07,964
- 18th: The mob is very wild.
- From 16th: 7th Regiment has arrived.

1458
02:21:08,127 --> 02:21:10,163
Foot of Canal, they are
on their way to Broadway.

1459
02:21:10,327 --> 02:21:11,521
Take your hands off me!

1460
02:21:11,687 --> 02:21:13,598
The mob is about 4500 strong.

1461
02:21:13,767 --> 02:21:16,725
They're going to burn down
Harlem Bridge. It is to be torched.

1462
02:21:16,887 --> 02:21:19,720
- Mr. Greeley!
- The rats have taken over the city!

1463
02:21:22,767 --> 02:21:26,396
From 21st: There is an attack on the
colored people in Second Avenue...

1464
02:21:26,567 --> 02:21:29,639
Mob headed for the Colored Orphans
Asylum. Protect the children!

1465
02:21:29,807 --> 02:21:31,479
Rioters on Seventh Avenue,
28th Street.

1466
02:21:32,847 --> 02:21:34,599
- They have killed a Negro.
- Get him!

1467
02:21:34,767 --> 02:21:36,883
What do we do with captured prisoners?

1468
02:21:37,047 --> 02:21:39,845
Prisoners? Don't take any.
The mob isn't taking prisoners!

1469
02:21:40,007 --> 02:21:43,317
Don't take a prisoner in
until you've put the mob down!

1470
02:21:50,327 --> 02:21:54,161
Soldiers now on 38th Street.
The mob will not disperse.

1471
02:21:54,327 --> 02:21:56,716
What are your orders?
What are your orders?

1472
02:22:10,847 --> 02:22:15,602
- No draft! No draft!
- Show them what we think of their draft!

1473
02:22:22,127 --> 02:22:23,685
- Stick together!
- All right.

1474
02:22:27,647 --> 02:22:29,683
Troop, halt!

1475
02:22:30,327 --> 02:22:32,716
Present arms!

1476
02:22:38,367 --> 02:22:39,800
On your order, Vallon.

1477
02:22:41,967 --> 02:22:43,719
Hold fast, there.
Hold fast, there.

1478
02:22:43,887 --> 02:22:46,606
I order you to disperse!

1479
02:22:49,727 --> 02:22:51,240
Fire!

1480
02:23:25,207 --> 02:23:27,402
Fire starboard!

1481
02:23:40,047 --> 02:23:42,766
Starboard battery, fire!

1482
02:23:51,967 --> 02:23:53,525
Come on, le�s go!

1483
02:23:59,607 --> 02:24:01,677
Fire over their heads!

1484
02:24:02,487 --> 02:24:04,557
Drive them into the square!

1485
02:24:07,207 --> 02:24:08,925
Bill!

1486
02:24:16,207 --> 02:24:17,526
Fire!

1487
02:24:18,167 --> 02:24:19,600
Advance!

1488
02:24:20,327 --> 02:24:22,158
Bill!

1489
02:24:25,127 --> 02:24:26,480
I can't walk!

1490
02:24:28,207 --> 02:24:29,686
Get up!

1491
02:25:30,647 --> 02:25:31,966
Fire!

1492
02:25:59,127 --> 02:26:02,802
- Bastards!
- Shang! Shang, hold off!

1493
02:26:33,847 --> 02:26:35,883
Thank God.

1494
02:26:36,807 --> 02:26:39,526
I die a true American.

1495
02:28:36,527 --> 02:28:38,961
Tomorrow morning,
get our people down to the docks.

1496
02:28:40,007 --> 02:28:44,364
I want every man and woman coming off
the boats given hot soup and bread.

1497
02:28:48,687 --> 02:28:52,043
We're burying a lot of votes
down here tonight.

1498
02:29:08,847 --> 02:29:13,477
In the end, they put candles
on the bodies so 's their friends...

1499
02:29:13,647 --> 02:29:17,686
...if they had any,
could know them in the dark.

1500
02:29:18,807 --> 02:29:22,117
The city did this free of charge.

1501
02:29:23,127 --> 02:29:28,918
Shang, Jimmy Spoils,
Hell-Cat, McGloin and more.

1502
02:29:30,367 --> 02:29:34,645
Friend or foe,
it didn 't make no difference now.

1503
02:29:53,367 --> 02:29:59,124
It was four days and nights before the
worst of the mob was finally put down.

1504
02:30:00,127 --> 02:30:02,687
We never knew how many
New Yorkers died that week...

1505
02:30:02,847 --> 02:30:05,520
...before the city was finally delivered.

1506
02:30:06,847 --> 02:30:11,716
My father told me we was all born
of blood and tribulation.

1507
02:30:12,807 --> 02:30:16,925
And so then too was our great city.

1508
02:30:19,727 --> 02:30:24,278
But for those of us what lived
and died in them furious days...

1509
02:30:24,447 --> 02:30:29,680
...it was like everything we knew
was mightily swept away.

1510
02:30:30,447 --> 02:30:33,439
And no matter what they did
to build the city up again...

1511
02:30:35,607 --> 02:30:38,167
...for the rest of time...

1512
02:30:39,087 --> 02:30:43,205
...it would be like no one even knew
we was ever here.

